                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by UsulDaNeriak[/i]
[br]i got scs long time ago, because i seldomly aggokite.
this AA rocks.

1. sitting on a horse in an exp group in BoT and casting FP, BOT, SK plus nukes without getting summoned or need to FD is a huge mana improvement.
2. even in LDoN no need to FD even if you cast BoT or Horror at contact. and FD costs mana!
3. one dot more in a row on raids before you need to FD. its all a siginificant save of mana and a big reducement on risk.

if you like to be a badass high dps high risk nec in fast killing exp groups, scs3 is a must. if not its at least nice to have.

and if you dont know how to aggo a mob while aggokiting, even with scs3, go make a druid.
i never had a problem to hold aggo, even if i seldomly aggokite.


Usul
